[[div class="modal"]]
[[span class="st"]]SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES:[[/span]] The interior of SCP-7912's chamber should remain empty and sealed. Further knowledge regarding containment of the anomaly is considered non-essential.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]**Tenebrarius:** The Foundation does not and cannot possess information about the anomaly.[[/span]]

[[/div]]

@@ @@

[[div class="modal"]]
[[span class="st"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] SCP-7912 refers to the interior of former Testing Chamber Alpha of the Pilcrow-Minkowski Center for Advanced Studies.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]Foundation black site facility responsible for the securement and research of anomalies with distinct, highly [[[scp-2921|complex]]] effect profiles/containment procedures.[[/span]] At this time, knowledge of the existence of SCP-7912 is limited to members of the Department of Deletions.  

SCP-7912's reference data does not exist; the sectors of the Database which lead to SCP-7912 have not been marked as read-only. Instead, a number of [[[scp-2719|abstract-metaphysical construct pointers]]] lead from writable whitespace to the identifier "interior of SCP-7912's chamber." This has been confirmed by Deletions agents, which observe the anomaly as empty void.

The origin of SCP-7912's current state is unknown. Due to its location, it is presumed to have been the result of testing or neutralization efforts of [[[scp-184|another]]] anomalous designation, the details of which were never documented.

The previous state of SCP-7912 is similarly unknown-- although assumptions can be made about its general layout and condition based on neighboring chambers, any concrete data about this topic is lost and unrecoverable. Attempts to fill these sectors with extrapolations have failed due to SCP-7912's apparent resistance to its own information; rather than seeking equilibrium within the surrounding area by naturally cohering to expected tropes and established rules of the fabula, SCP-7912 rejects all definition in a manner directly proportional to its own relevance.[[span class="fnnum"]].[[/span]][[span class="fncon"]]A notable violation of the Ockham-Hitchens Proposition. Specifically, between non sequitur and apagoge; ie. "The relationship between the most likely cause and its inherent truth is typically linear." More information can be found in the included testing log.[[/span]]

