[[div class="jotting modal tableb"]]
= [[span class="st"]]ADDENDUM 7912/I[[/span]]

----

[[table]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
[[span class="bt"]]ON THE CONTAINMENT OF SCP-7912[[/span]]
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[cell]]

[[span class="bt"]]LOCATION:[[/span]] {{RESEARCH STATION MNEMOSYNE}}
[[span class="bt"]]PARTIES PRESENT:[[/span]] {{THE DEPARTMENT OF DELETIONS, in pentaplicate}}

[[span class="bt"]]PREFACE:[[/span]] {{DELETIONS AGENTS MEET WITHIN RESEARCH STATION MNEMOSYNE TO DISCUSS POTENTIAL CONTAINMENT STRATEGIES OF SCP-7912.}}
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
«BEGIN TRANSCRIPT»
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[<]]
= //<Conference room materializes. A moment later, a vague humanoid form occupies the far end of a long table in the center. The entity's features shift chaotically. It stretches before emitting a large sigh, turning its indeterminate form slightly to the left.>//

[[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A:##[[/span]] We should do this more often. Why don't we do this more often?

= //<Another entity manifests in the chair [[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A##[[/span]] faces. It also possesses the same instability but leans back in the chair, relaxed.>// 

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] Because it's insane. This is quite literally delusional. I'd call it masturbatory but, for some reason, I'm against the idea of roasting you //too// hard. All of this pretense is a waste of-- 

[[span class="bt"]]##5c5b8e|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Disembodied.>// Time? You know that word has little meaning here. And please, don't act like you have anything else better to do.

= //<A third humanoid appears across the table from the second, on [[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A##[[/span]]'s right.>//

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] We wouldn't be here if there wasn't something better to do. 


[[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Coughs.>// Well, that's exactly why I've arranged this meeting; as you can probably tell, you exist again, which means we have a new assignment. 

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] So, holding a department-wide, in-person meeting is purely symbolic? 


[[span class="bt"]]##5c5b8e|N/A:##[[/span]] No, it's done for the "internal debate." //<Scoffs.>// 

[[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A:##[[/span]] Laugh all you want. I'm aware of the shortcomings of this format, but you are also aware we parse some things out better like this.

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] Usually, it's not necessary. I mean, //usually//, our tasks are somewhat clear, as complicated as they may be.

[[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A:##[[/span]] Not today. We have a gravity well in the Database that needs to be filled, and I'm sure you understand the issue with that sentiment. 

[[span class="bt"]]##5c5b8e|N/A:##[[/span]] Of course.

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] //It's all information, baby.//

[[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A:##[[/span]] Right. If it can destroy its own information, nothing we put there will last. It lacks read-only protection, lacks true understanding. The fact that we're discussing it right now in these plain of terms means we haven't interacted with the timeline in a way that would have impacted us, nor will we at any point. I'm not sure if we //can// interact with it now, even though we all can see the open window.

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] We have to overwrite our memories. Leave a note for the next iteration.

[[span class="bt"]]##5c5b8e|N/A:##[[/span]] You don't know that--

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] No, I //do// know that. We all know that, avoiding the inevitable is just easier, isn't it? Sitting here, getting all chummy with ourselves, throwing this little pity party for less than one. You've been getting too comfortable. We all have. We're not supposed to get comfortable here. I'm ready to move on.

[[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A:##[[/span]] Wait--Wait. Let me just get a second opinion. 

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Snorts.>// Hilarious.

= //<Two more entities, a fourth and a fifth, condense into corporeality in the next two seats, identical to the others. One rests its elbows on the table, head in hands, while the other fidgets uncomfortably, left knee jittering with nervous energy. None of the five members notice the man sitting in the back of the room, transcribing this document.>//

[[span class="bt"]]##ff8b6f|N/A:##[[/span]] What do you hope for me to add to the conversation, man? Let me go back to the void, for fuck's sake. 

[[span class="bt"]]##444b47|N/A:##[[/span]] Shush. Let's just get this over with.

[[span class="bt"]]##5c5b8e|N/A:##[[/span]] Er--yeah. And don't stretch us too thin. Although, I agree with you that there has to be something else we can try before reformat. //<Turning to [[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A##[[/span]].>// Not because I'm attached to these people but because I think it's a stupid idea. 

[[span class="bt"]]##ba5258|N/A:##[[/span]] I beg your pardon?

[[span class="bt"]]##5c5b8e|N/A:##[[/span]] We don't know what would happen if our department came into contact with a metaconceptual hazard. I was certain it wasn't possible until a moment ago--Hold on. Where did that information come from?

[[span class="bt"]]##ff8b6f|N/A:##[[/span]] Don't look at us. We aren't new to this mode of existence.

[[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A:##[[/span]] Wait, this can't be right. Fragmentation levels are the same. No foreign memories, no dead sectors. How is this possible?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] //<Standing.>// That would probably be me, sorry. I was hoping it would be more... subtle.

[[span class="bt"]]##744758|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Looking up, surprised.>// How--? Who are you?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Well...

= //<[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A##[[/span]] peers over at the other entity, who stares back at the empty conference room. The space dissolves and is replaced by a small cell moments later. A single table and two chairs furnish the blank space, [[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A##[[/span]] occupying the seat across from [[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912##[[/span]].>//

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] Who //are// you?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] //<Sitting in chair opposite [[span class="bt"]]##white|N/A##[[/span]].>// My name is Andry. I'm from the Department of Deletions. 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] That cannot be true. //We// are Deletions. You are something else entirely.

= //<[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912##[[/span]] smirks. He maintains a rough resemblance of someone, a researcher named Andry, who once existed, somewhere, but not anymore. It didn't matter. All that mattered was his intact Semblance. He was __someone__, something no other member of Deletions could say with such conviction.>// 

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] I'm an inevitability; my presence an eventual outcome given the nature of the Database. My patchwork is whole. You must understand what I'm saying.

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] You--//<Pauses.>// Your identity is separate, because it is complete.

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Bingo. 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] This- This is unprecedented. You're an anomaly among anomalies. The chances of something like this occurring are... //<Pauses.>// Two hundred and ninety-four million to one.

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] And yet, here I am.

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] How?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Unfortunately, statistics is not the only factor at play here. You've deleted me before. Well, not //you//, you. Previous iterations of you. The cause of this... //deviation// eludes me, but I assure you, it is well beyond the scope of probabilities. As you said; unprecedented.

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] Well... Let's just say I'm not used to having company.

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] What about your little troupe, are they not company enough?

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] The line that separates you from I is far more tangible than that which separates the rest of us. That delineation was lost before introduction. It's far less unpredictable, far more mundane.

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] I expected something to that effect. I keep thinking you'll be different but existential boredom seems to be a constant around these parts. 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] I'm sorry, but I still don't understand why you showed yourself here, now. 

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] //<Putting feet up on the table.>// Your little problem. That gravity well. I've been trying to figure it out, we have. You keep overwriting parts of yourself to get around the effect, but have grown quite proficient at being exposed.

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Rubbing temples.>// How do I know you're telling the truth? You could just as easily be another Database error we're trying to contain. It's far more likely than the story you've presented.

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Yes, that's the problem, isn't it? The unlikelihood is proof of its certainty. 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Shakes head.>// What?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] //<Sighs.>// Here. 

= //<[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912##[[/span]] hands [[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A##[[/span]] a series of documents.>//

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] This is all the experiential data we have about the anomaly. At some point, a neutralization attempt of SCP-184 took place within the P.M. Center. We don't know why, nor how. We can't even be sure this was the result. But it makes sense in a nonsensical way, doesn't it?

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Reading.>// Not really, no. 

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] What is the inverse of something that duplicates an interior with increasing inaccuracy the farther you move outward? 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] Something that removes an interior with increasing accuracy the farther you travel inward? I mean, I //guess//--Wait, so, what happened to 184?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Your guess is probably better than mine, the fact of the matter is we can't know for sure without being completely unsure. I believe this is unlikely to be attributable to the chamber's [[[scp-4972|Adaptive Mesh]]], because that would be the most apt explanation, you see? 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] Yeesh. Okay, so, how can we even discuss this? You've clearly encountered this anomaly before, you claim the metaconceptual hazard can affect us, wouldn't that mean this thing can't be discussed outright? 

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] You're fine, for now. Like you said, you haven't interacted with the timeline yet. I have, but because of our unique position, my cognitive faculties are the ones at risk here. 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] And yet, we keep exposing ourselves.

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Yes, you keep ignoring my warning.

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] Warning? What warning?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] //<Taking feet off the table and leaning forward.>// Do not go through SCP-7912. It must remain sealed. Everything will be fine if you stay here. 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] And you?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] I haven't gone through it yet, but I know I will. I also know my Semblance remains whole after that point, as it has throughout my many deletions. A few specks of data are lost, here and there, but I have never once lost anything I cared about losing. 

= //<[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A##[[/span]] disappears and reappears, now standing behind the chair, hand resting on it. The entity vanishes once more and five take its place, debating quietly in a tight huddle. A moment later they melt into the floor. [[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A##[[/span]] manifests back in the chair, shifting quickly as if agitated.>//

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Is there a problem?

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] No. Thinking. We'll need a better understanding of what happens inside the chamber. Can we get a camera working in there? 

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Hm. //<Pauses.>// A surprisingly novel idea. I believe I can, yes. It would have to be embedded in the Mesh itself, which is doable.

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] Right, you keep mentioning an adaptive mesh. What is it?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Well, it's a mesh that adapts to things. That doesn't make sense?

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] No--It- I thought there would be more to it than that.

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] None whatsoever. Oh, I did manage to switch it off once. I think. It's probably still off, considering. 

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Surprised.>// Why would you do that?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] You can't all be this fucking dense, can you? How should I know?! I barely have context for this. All I know is that it //was// off, and I know how to turn it back //on//. But I //haven't//. That enough for you?

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] Look, we just want to understand your perspective. We usually have no problem getting to know each other.

//<[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912##[[/span]] stares, wearily. A pained expression crosses his face. After a moment, it passes and he speaks again.>//

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] //<Sighs.>// You're right. Maybe I should try something new. If it doesn't work, it's just a matter of time before you forget me anyway, right?

//<The defined figure does not wait for a response to the rhetorical and continues.>//

In truth, I'm the one making this dynamic weird and //also// the one leaving you in the dark. It was your preference. These memories are painful, but I still hold them and the weight of their burden. Someone has to.

I was--I am one of SCP-184's neutralization team. Out of them, I'm the only one whose identity hasn't been fragmented to shit. The rest of them... the rest of those people and the rest of that anomaly is //gone//. Gone //here//. They're you.  

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] How--?

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] When it, uh, //happened//, you were mostly yourselves. One gestalt sure, but, you knew each other's names. And mine. You could form us separate and that separation was so profound. We were lost in this state. I mean, the things you could do with that dodecahedron inside you. You'd have not believed it. 

A conference room? A holding cell? //<Scoffs.>// Think of floating castles, arboretums in the clouds, skyscrapers above them. Orangeries on their rooftop gardens. Infinitely. Our power was infinite. Or so we thought.

We began to worry about that place, that hole in nothing that can be anything, so long as it wasn't the right thing. We started seeing it, in daydreams, when we closed our eyes. A vast and pulsating void, I would feel myself sink into an ocean of tar, where every direction of escape was wrong and led further downhill, further into darkness. The liquid would climb up my body and pour itself into my mouth and nose... I could feel every sensation. I'd never been so frightened. 

We decided to start looking, not knowing what we'd do with it. Do we jump back in, fully changed to the state we are now, or does the nature and direction of time preclude that possibility? Were there states worse than this one we'd been given as mercy?

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] So, you couldn't do it.

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] //<Stands, enraged.>// No, //we// couldn't do it! You were there too, but only the physical images. You had figured out how to 'reformat' parts of your data so you could be unburdened by your ego, unburdened by your visions. Your memories. Abusing the same methods we used to improperly neutralize 184 in the first place. You'd leave instruction--

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] --Instructions for the next iteration, yes. It's a stopgap measure. To prevent exposure. 

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] //<Approaches [[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A##[[/span]].>// You fools. It was guilt you were exposing yourself to, guilt over abandoning your Assignment, and myself. Weakness. You're weak. And too scared to do what needs to be done. 

I will do what needs to be done. And as long as you stay on this side of the Barrier, you'll be safe from the hazardous effects, remember? Well, except each others'. 

= //<[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A##[[/span]] looks down in surprise, noticing their feet melting into the floor, along with [[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912's##[[/span]].>//

[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912:##[[/span]] Turns out we both know how to design an interior. Don't worry, undoing it is easy; ever solve a Rubik's Cube for the first time? Know what, your answer doesn't really matter at this point.

You'll know when I have installed the cameras. Until then. Don't be a stranger. 

= //<[[span class="bt"]]##783a8d|POI-7912##[[/span]] disappears into the floor.>//

[[span class="bt"]]##fdf1f2|N/A:##[[/span]] //<Struggling.>// What did you do? Why can't I move?! Andry!
[[/<]]
